The paper deals with testing high-dimensional structured distributions, specifically Bayesian networks. This involves concepts from machine learning, statistics, and information theory. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also involves algorithms and computational complexity, which suggests cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) as a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with graphical models, which could fall under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
